AMENDMENTS TO LB972
(Amendments to E&R amendments, ER132)
Introduced by Moser, 22.
1 1. Strike section 51 and insert the following new sections:
2 Sec. 51. Section 60-3,163.02, Revised Statutes Supplement, 2025, is
3 amended to read:
4 60-3,163.02 The department shall issue the following types of
5 alternate license plates pursuant to this section and sections 60-3,104,
6 60-3,163, and 60-3,163.01:
7 (1) Arbor Day Plates. The department shall design such license
8 plates in consultation with the Nebraska Statewide Arboretum and a
9 nonprofit organization holding a certificate of exemption under section
10 501(c)(3) of the Internal Revenue Code with a mission to inspire people
11 to plant, nurture, and celebrate trees. The design of such plates shall
12 represent the history and importance of Arbor Day in Nebraska. The
13 designated recipient for alternate license plate fees for Arbor Day
14 Plates is the Home of Arbor Day Plate Cash Fund . A person may apply for
15 Arbor Day Plates beginning on January 1, 2026;
16 (2) Back the Blue License Plates. The department shall design such
17 license plates in consultation with associations that represent personnel
18 of any law enforcement agency in Nebraska. The design of such license
19 plates shall represent support for law enforcement personnel. The
20 designated recipient for alternate license plate fees for Back the Blue
21 License Plates is the Back the Blue Cash Fund. A person may apply for
22 Back the Blue License Plates beginning on January 1, 2027;
23 (3) Blackout License Plates. The department shall design such
24 license plates so that (a) a solid black background covers the entire
25 front of the license plates and (b) the license plate designations use
26 white characters. Each application for initial issuance or renewal or
-1-

AM2844 AM2844
LB972 LB972
MJP - 03/19/2026 MJP - 03/19/2026
1 alphanumeric or personalized message Blackout License Plates shall be
2 accompanied by a fee of one hundred dollars. The designated recipient for
3 alternate license plate fees for Blackout License Plates is the
4 Developmental Disabilities Provider Capital and Equipment Maintenance
5 Cash Fund. Fees collected pursuant to this subdivision shall be remitted
6 to the State Treasurer. The State Treasurer shall credit thirty percent
7 of such fees to the designated recipient for alternate license plate fees
8 and seventy percent of such fees to the Department of Motor Vehicles Cash
9 Fund. A person may apply for Blackout License Plates beginning on January
10 1, 2027;
11 (4) (2) Breast Cancer Awareness Plates. The department shall design
12 such license plates to include a pink ribbon and the words "early
13 detection saves lives" along the bottom of the license plate. The
14 designated recipient for alternate license plate fees for Breast Cancer
15 Awareness Plates is the University of Nebraska Medical Center for the
16 breast cancer navigator program;
17 (5) Choice Color Plates. The department shall design two of such
18 license plates so that (a) a single solid-color background covers the
19 entire front of the license plates and (b) the license plate designations
20 use white characters. The options for single solid-color backgrounds
21 shall be green and blue. Each application for initial issuance or renewal
22 of alphanumeric Choice Color Plates shall be accompanied by a fee of
23 seventy dollars. Each application for initial issuance or renewal of
24 personalized message Choice Color Plates shall be accompanied by a fee of
25 one hundred dollars. The designated recipient for alternate license plate
26 fees for Choice Color Plates is the Department of Motor Vehicles Cash
27 Fund. Fees collected pursuant to this subdivision shall be remitted to
28 the State Treasurer. The State Treasurer shall credit one hundred percent
29 of such fees to the designated recipient for alternate license plate
30 fees. A person may apply for Choice Color Plates beginning on January 1,
31 2027;
-2-

AM2844 AM2844
LB972 LB972
MJP - 03/19/2026 MJP - 03/19/2026
1 (6) (3) Choose Life License Plates. The department shall design such
2 license plates to reflect support for the protection of Nebraska's
3 children. The designated recipient for alternate license plate fees for
4 Choose Life License Plates is the Health and Human Services Cash Fund to
5 supplement federal funds available to the Department of Health and Human
6 Services for the Temporary Assistance for Needy Families program, 42
7 U.S.C. 601 et seq.;
8 (7) (4) Czech Heritage Plates. The department, in consultation with
9 the Czech Honorary Consul of Nebraska, shall design such license plates
10 to reflect Czech heritage in Nebraska. The designated recipient for
11 alternate license plate fees for Czech Heritage Plates is the Department
12 of Motor Vehicles Cash Fund;
13 (8) (5) Donate Life Plates. The department shall design such license
14 plates to reflect support for organ and tissue donation, registration as
15 a donor on the Donor Registry of Nebraska, and the federally designated
16 organ procurement organization for Nebraska. The designated recipient for
17 alternate license plate fees for Donate Life Plates is the Organ and
18 Tissue Donor Awareness and Education Fund;
19 (9) (6) Down Syndrome Awareness Plates. The department shall design
20 such license plates to include the words "Down syndrome awareness" inside
21 a heart-shaped yellow and blue ribbon. The designated recipient for
22 alternate license plate fees for Down Syndrome Awareness Plates is the
23 University of Nebraska Medical Center for the Down Syndrome Clinic;
24 (10) Honoring Women Veterans. The department shall design such
25 license plates, in consultation with a nongovernment organization that
26 provides support to veterans, to depict a woman soldier and to include
27 the words "women veterans" along the top of the license plates and
28 "honoring her service" along the bottom of the license plates. The
29 designated recipient for Honoring Women Veterans license plates is the
30 Women Veterans Cash Fund. A person may apply for Honoring Women Veterans
31 license plates beginning on January 1, 2027;
-3-

