1 (b)(i) Each application for initial issuance or renewal of
2 alphanumeric Support Our Troops Plates shall be accompanied by a fee of
3 five dollars. The State Treasurer shall credit five dollars of the fee to
4 the designated recipient for alternate license plate fees for Support Our
5 Troops Plates.
6 (ii) Each application for initial issuance or renewal of
7 personalized message Support Our Troops Plates shall be accompanied by a
8 fee of seventy dollars. Twenty-five percent of such fee shall be credited
9 to the Department of Motor Vehicles Cash Fund and seventy-five percent of
10 such fee shall be credited to the designated recipient for alternate
11 license plate fees for Support Our Troops Plates;
12 (22) (17) The Good Life Is Outside Plates. The department shall
13 design such license plates to reflect the importance of safe walking and
14 biking in Nebraska and the value of our recreational trails. The
15 designated recipient for alternate license plate fees for The Good Life
16 Is Outside Plates is the Game and Parks State Park Improvement and
17 Maintenance Fund for the purpose of trail improvement and maintenance;
18 and
19 (23) University of Nebraska State Museum License Plates. The
20 department shall create no more than three designs for such license
21 plates in consultation with the University of Nebraska and a nonprofit
22 organization holding a certificate of exemption under section 501(c)(3)
23 of the Internal Revenue Code with a mission to support the University of
24 Nebraska in education and research. Such designs shall reflect support
25 for museums managed by the University of Nebraska, including Ashfall
26 Fossil Beds, Morrill Hall, and Trailside Museum. The designated recipient
27 for alternate license plate fees for University of Nebraska State Museum
28 License Plates is the University of Nebraska State Museum License Plate
29 Cash Fund. A person may apply for University of Nebraska State Museum
30 License Plates beginning on January 1, 2027; and
31 (24) (18) Wildlife Conservation Plates. The department shall create
