1 no more than three designs for such license plates to reflect support for
2 the conservation of Nebraska wildlife, including sandhill cranes, bighorn
3 sheep, and ornate box turtles. The designated recipient for alternate
4 license plate fees for Wildlife Conservation Plates is the Wildlife
5 Conservation Fund.
6 Sec. 77. (1) The Back the Blue Cash Fund is created and shall be
7 administered by the Nebraska State Patrol. The fund shall consist of
8 gifts, grants, bequests, money received from any public or private
9 source, money credited pursuant to section 60-3,163.02, and money
10 transferred to the fund by the Legislature.
11 (2) Any money in the fund available for investment shall be invested
12 by the state investment officer pursuant to the Nebraska Capital
13 Expansion Act and the Nebraska State Funds Investment Act. Any interest
14 or realized capital gains from any such investment shall be credited to
15 the Back the Blue Cash Fund.
16 (3)(a) The fund shall only be used pursuant to this section.
17 (b) The Nebraska State Patrol may award grants from the fund
18 pursuant to section 78 of this act.
19 (c) The fund shall not be used for buying any equipment for or
20 paying any salary or cost for the Nebraska State Patrol.
21 Sec. 78. (1) For purposes of this section:
22 (a) Eligible purpose means:
23 (i) Providing support to any:
24 (A) Injured law enforcement personnel;
25 (B) Spouse of any injured or deceased law enforcement personnel; or
26 (C) Child of any injured or deceased law enforcement personnel if
27 such child is under the age of nineteen years old; or
28 (ii) Conducting any charitable activity that supports the residents
29 of this state; and
30 (b) Qualified applicant means any association that represents
31 personnel of any law enforcement agency in this state.
-8-

AM2844 AM2844
LB972 LB972
MJP - 03/19/2026 MJP - 03/19/2026
1 (2) A qualified applicant may apply to the Nebraska State Patrol for
2 a grant under this section. The Nebraska State Patrol shall prescribe the
3 form for the application.
4 (3) The Nebraska State Patrol may award a grant to any qualified
5 applicant who applies under this section for an eligible purpose.
6 (4) The State of Nebraska shall not require or request any recipient
7 of a grant awarded under this section to reimburse any money received
8 from such grant.
9 (5) No later than January 1, 2027, the Nebraska State Patrol shall
10 prescribe the form for grant applications under this section.
11 (6) The Nebraska State Patrol may adopt and promulgate rules and
12 regulations to carry out this section.
13 Sec. 79. (1) The Developmental Disabilities Provider Capital and
14 Equipment Maintenance Cash Fund is created and shall be administered by
15 the Department of Health and Human Services. The fund shall consist of
16 gifts, grants, bequests, money received from any public or private
17 source, money credited pursuant to section 60-3,163.02, and money
18 transferred to the fund by the Legislature.
19 (2) Any money in the fund available for investment shall be invested
20 by the state investment officer pursuant to the Nebraska Capital
21 Expansion Act and the Nebraska State Funds Investment Act.
22 (3)(a) The fund shall only be used pursuant to this section.
23 (b) The Department of Health and Human Services may award grants
24 from the fund pursuant to section 80 of this act.
25 (c) The fund shall not be used for the general operation or
26 administration of the state's developmental disabilities program.
27 Sec. 80. (1) For purposes of this section:
28 (a) Department means the Department of Health and Human Services;
29 (b) Eligible purpose means any upgrade, modernization, renovation,
30 maintenance, or new purchase of the following that are used by a provider
31 to provide any developmental disability service:
-9-

AM2844 AM2844
LB972 LB972
MJP - 03/19/2026 MJP - 03/19/2026
1 (i) The transportation fleet that is used to provide support to or
2 to transport any individual with a developmental disability;
3 (ii) Any physical infrastructure or safety feature, including any
4 feature that is used to reinforce any space that is used to provide any
5 developmental disability service, safety glass, any perimeter security
6 feature, and any other physical improvement that is meant to protect any
7 client or staff member of a provider;
8 (iii) Any technology or remote-support infrastructure that is used
9 to support or monitor any client, staff member, or facility
10 infrastructure of a provider. Such technology or remote-support
11 infrastructure includes any sensor, smart-home automation feature, and
12 broadband infrastructure; and
13 (iv) Any facility to increase capacity for clients or optimize space
14 that is available for clients or the provision of any developmental
15 disability service, including any facility floorplan efficiency
16 improvement and installation of any amenity or restroom; and
17 (c) Provider means any entity that is under contract with the
18 department to provide any specialized or assisted service under section
19 83-1217.
20 (2) A provider may apply to the department for a grant under this
21 section. The department shall prescribe the form for the application.
22 (3) The department may award a grant to any qualified applicant who
23 applies under this section for an eligible purpose.
24 (4) No later than January 1, 2027, the department shall prescribe
25 the form for grant applications under this section.
26 (5) The department may adopt and promulgate rules and regulations to
27 carry out this section.
28 2. On page 91, line 15, strike "78" and insert "82".
29 3. Renumber the remaining sections accordingly.
